## рџљЂ Quick start

### 1 вЂ” Requirements
- PHP 8.0+ with `mysqli`, `curl`, `gd` extensions
- MySQL 5.7+ or MariaDB 10.4+
- Your Python AI engine running on `http://127.0.0.1:5000` (optional вЂ” system works standalone)

### 2 вЂ” Drop the file into your project
```
attendance_system/
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ attendance.php          в†ђ this file
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ attendance_dashboard.html
в””в”Ђв”Ђ snapshots/              в†ђ auto-created on first snapshot
```

### 3 вЂ” Edit the config block (top of file)
```php
define('DB_HOST', 'localhost');
define('DB_USER', 'root');      // your MySQL username
define('DB_PASS', '');          // your MySQL password
define('DB_NAME', 'attendance_db');
```

### 4 вЂ” Create the database tables
Open `attendance.php` in your browser в†’ click the **DB setup** tab в†’ click **Run now via PHP**.

Or manually paste the SQL into phpMyAdmin / MySQL Workbench.

### 5 вЂ” Open it
```
http://localhost/attendance_system/attendance.php
```

---

## рџ”Њ REST API (AJAX endpoints)

All endpoints are on the same URL вЂ” pass `action` as a POST or GET parameter.

| Action | Method | Parameters | Returns |
|---|---|---|---|
| `save_snapshot` | POST | `image` (base64 data-URL), `label` | `{ok, id, filename, url}` |
| `list_snapshots` | GET | `page`, `per_page` | `{snapshots[], total}` |
| `delete_snapshot` | POST | `id` | `{ok, deleted}` |
| `log_attendance` | POST | `student_id`, `name`, `class`, `confidence`, `status`, `snapshot_file` | `{ok, id}` |
| `get_attendance` | GET | `date`, `class` | `{records[]}` |
| `get_stats` | GET | вЂ” | `{stats}` |
| `add_student` | POST | `name`, `roll_number`, `class`, `email` | `{ok, id}` |
| `list_students` | GET | `search`, `class` | `{students[]}` |
| `ai_status` | GET | вЂ” | `{online: bool}` |

### Example вЂ” log attendance from Python
```python
import requests

requests.post('http://localhost/attendance_system/attendance.php', data={
    'action':        'log_attendance',
    'student_id':    'CS21001',
    'name':          'Arjun Mehta',
    'class':         'CSE-A',
    'confidence':    96.4,
    'status':        'present',
    'snapshot_file': '20250610_090312_session-start.jpg',
})
```

### Example вЂ” save a snapshot from Python (OpenCV frame)
```python
import requests, base64, cv2

_, buf = cv2.imencode('.jpg', frame)
b64 = base64.b64encode(buf).decode()

requests.post('http://localhost/attendance_system/attendance.php', data={
    'action': 'save_snapshot',
    'image':  f'data:image/jpeg;base64,{b64}',
    'label':  'auto-capture',
})
```

